Emacs interfaces to the spelling checker program, called ispell, and you can use it to spell-check a single word, a region, or a whole buffer.
on-the-fly spell-checking: wheneve you type a word, it is spell-checked and, if it contains errors, the word is hightlighted and you are offered a menu of suggestions
Basic spelling commands: exit-ispell-word(M-$), ispell-region, and ispell-buffer.
